<font color="#FF0000">THE GOD OF WAR AND AMNESTY </font><br>
<tt>Sun Sep 14 10:31:29 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Tom;<br>
The people that feared and trembled did not need forgiveness, in the eyes of God they had not sinned. It was within their nature and what is a normal behavior in some God nor Gideon condemned nor did those people need to be forgiven. For what? What did these people do wrong? They feared and trembled and there is nothing wrong with that. They and those that feared to go to war during the Vietnam War did nothing wrong, they did nothing wrong to be forgiven for. Spatz did nothing wrong to be forgiven for.<br><br>
What is wrong is when some of them attacked those that did go to war. God snuffed off some of the spies send into the Promised Land because they discouraged others from going against the giants of the land. When you see the need and you respond for the good of others and then some come along and question your involvement and attack your intervention because they failed to react, because they feared and trembled that's what's wrong. <br><br>
MTF, Tatekohomni Wambli, little humming bird<br><br>
Sorry, buddy but, yes, God is a God of War, he might even be a Jarhead, has a fancy brighter, shiner uniform and wears all types of crowns on His head. Guess what? They were all won in battle against the forces of evil, Satan and his demons. That's why you like Him so much. It's His love for mankind, (even chopper pilots) that makes him the God of mercy and forgiveness. <br>
God is a God of War; he has been fighting injustice, sin and sickness  and evil through men for decades. We have the capability to do BOTH good and evil. The law enforcement officer is there for the good of the people but when he shoots to kill and not to stop he has overstepped his authority.<br>
I'm afraid that if Tom were to examine the scriptures he would find God listed on the top of the Winter Soldiers list of individuals charged with committing atrocities against human beings. After all he often ordered His people to go into villages and different lands and kill all the men, women and children. <br>
On the surface we're amazed that he would order such a thing until we see why he ordered their destruction, it is then we realize who he is and why he waged war against those people. We then understand what trueand pure  justice is.<br>
Was God in Vietnam? He was there with every tracer I fired and every round that was fired back at me. He was there with Murphy, Bro, Stoker,Ira, and many others. He was there with O'Neil as doc worked frantically trying to save his life, stuffing the shinny silvery foil from the gum wrappers I was peeling off into O'Neil's chest trying to plug up the hole in his chest. He was there with all those wounded in their bodies and in their minds and in their hearts. He was there with Lucero as I fired inches over his head while he laid at the foot of the trench line where the gooks had dragged him to use as a shield. He was there last February when I spoke to Lucero again for the first time in over thirty years, thirty years of suffering and shame he had endured before someone spoke to him about what an honorable warrior he was. He cried then, as honorable men do when finally someone understands what they had gone through, something his own county has yet to recognize. <br>
Neither God nor Gideon ever offered amnesty to those who arose against those who did go to battle; instead God destroyed them and their children. I don't know what God called them, What does God call people he's about to destroy.<br>
Yes! God was in Nam, He was there all along and I just didn't know it, but that's another book for another time. <br><br>
Barry Spatz,<br>
Fishing I have found is an art, I've never been able to catch fish for some reason. I once did catch one off the Santa Monica Pier. A nice big beautiful and very colorful fish, (probably even had a coin in his mouth) but this guy came along to help and the fish fell off the line. One day I'll try fishing again. I learned to respect fishermen and not interfere with them while they are fishing in a spot they have chosen. Sometimes fish don't stay on the same side of the lake, some of them swim from one side of the lake to the other and the other fishermen get a chance to try and catch the fish, sometimes the fish takes a bite then returns to the other side of the lake. If the other fishermen catches the fish I was fishing for that doesn't bother me. What bothered me is when a guy throws in a grenade and the fish all blotted and torn raise to the surface and that guy calls it fishing, that's what bothers me.<br><br>

